  <description>Stems to 0.6 cm diam., stipitate-glandular; bristles present; bark usually peeling with age. Leaves: petiole stipitate-glandular; leaflets 3--5, terminal ovate to lanceolate, base rounded to cordate, unlobed or lobed (less deeply so in ternate leaves), apex acuminate to attenuate, abaxial surfaces stipitate-glandular. Flowers: sepals stipitate-glandular. Fruits: drupelets 10--60, coherent, separating without torus attached or drupelets not coherent and falling separately. 2n = 14, 21, 28.</description>
